# === THE ONE MANUAL STEP ===
# 1. Copy this file to `.env`   ->   Copy-Item .env.example .env
# 2. Paste your GitHub Copilot access-token below (the ONLY thing you do by hand).
#
# Get the token from a machine that's already working:
#     (macOS)   cat ~/.config/litellm/github_copilot/access-token
#     (Windows) Get-Content "$env:USERPROFILE\.config\litellm\github_copilot\access-token"
# It starts with  ghu_  (or gho_).
#
# PASTE IT RAW: no surrounding quotes, no trailing spaces. Save this file as UTF-8;
# a trailing CRLF is fine (install.ps1 strips \r), but no quotes.
#
# This seeds the proxy so this machine does NOT need a GitHub OAuth/2FA login.
# It's your own token on your own device.

COPILOT_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ---- optional ----
# Pin the local gateway password (guards only the 127.0.0.1:4000 proxy; NOT a real
# secret). If unset, a random one is generated and reused across runs.
# LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=

# Force a runtime. Default is native Python (easiest on Windows — no WSL/Docker).
# Docker Desktop is used only with -Docker or if a docker engine is already running.
# NOTE: the -Python / -Docker install.ps1 switches OVERRIDE this line.
# RUNTIME=docker
# RUNTIME=python
